abstract: Republicans and Democrats laid out their visions of health care beyond the Affordable Care Act: a single-payer system or state government control.
snippet: Republicans and Democrats laid out their visions of health care beyond the Affordable Care Act: a single-payer system or state government control.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In one Senate office building, some of the leading lights of the Democratic Party gathered Wednesday to embrace what was once a proposal only of the far left: a huge expansion of Medicare, large enough to open the popular, government-run health program to all Americans.

abstract: Well before most of them will announce they are running, prospective Democratic candidates for president are taking steps to lay the financial foundation for a campaign.
snippet: Well before most of them will announce they are running, prospective Democratic candidates for president are taking steps to lay the financial foundation for a campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Aides to Senator Kamala Harris of California say that her fund-raisers in Martha’s Vineyard and the Hamptons this summer have been all about helping Democrats in 2018. Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s allies say his new political group is building an email list so he can communicate directly with his supporters about the future of the party and the country. And Representative Tim Ryan of Ohio says he has been traveling to Iowa and New Hampshire in part because “I like being out around the country.”

headline_main: California Today: Clashes, Again, in Berkeley

abstract: There’s a little bail reform bill, but Dog’s wife doesn’t like it and the senator she calls “sort of anti-American” does.
snippet: There’s a little bail reform bill, but Dog’s wife doesn’t like it and the senator she calls “sort of anti-American” does.
lead_paragraph: One of my fond childhood memories is going to the amusement park in Cincinnati on Republican Day. My grandfather, who was a bail bondsman, organized the outings so I could ride on the rides and he could play cards in a tent with the judges. To whom he would systematically lose.

abstract: Survivors in Freetown, the capital, resorted to stacking bodies on soccer fields, after heavy rain and mudslides killed as many as 200 people.
snippet: Survivors in Freetown, the capital, resorted to stacking bodies on soccer fields, after heavy rain and mudslides killed as many as 200 people.
lead_paragraph: DAKAR, Senegal — Torrents of water rushed through the streets of the Sierra Leone capital of Freetown on Monday, causing mudslides that killed hundreds and trapped hundreds more in their homes and vehicles, officials said.
